# Flexbox Full Page Layout

This exercise demonstrates how to use Flexbox to structure a complete web page layout including a header, footer, and centered main content.

## ðŸ“Œ Objectives
- Create a responsive full-page layout using Flexbox
- Position header at the top and footer at the bottom of the viewport
- Center main content vertically and horizontally
- Distribute links to opposite sides of the header and footer
- Add proper spacing and styling to match a clean UI

## ðŸ’¡ Key Flex Concepts Used
- `display: flex` with `flex-direction: column`
- `justify-content` and `align-items`
- `gap`, `padding`, and spacing utilities
- Removing default styles from lists and links

## âœ… Self Check
- Header and footer are sticky at top and bottom
- Spacing and alignment between all elements is correct
- Input and buttons are centered and styled properly
- No floats, inline-block, or absolute positioning used
